@startuml
Digidoclocker — Polished Requirement Specification

Functional Requirements
1. UserTypeIdentification
2. CitizenRegistration
3. CorrectLogin
4. ProfileManagement
5. ContinuedDocumentUploads
6. MultipleCertificateApplications
7. RegistrarRequests
8. RegistrarMultipleRequests
9. SessionEnd

UserTypeIdentification[*] --> Registration

state Registration
Registration : entry / Get the User Details
Registration : do / Validate the Details
Registration : exit / Citizen or Registrar

Registration --> [*] : [Citizen]
Registration --> RegistrarRequest : [Registrar]

state RegistrarRequest
RegistrarRequest : entry / Request for Certificates
RegistrarRequest : do / Validate the Details
RegistrarRequest : exit / Request Sent

RegistrarRequest --> [*] : [End]


state Citizen
Citizen : entry / Logged In
Citizen : do / Display Options
Citizen : exit / End Session

Citizen --> DocumentUpload : [Upload Documents]
Citizen --> CertificateApplication : [Apply for a Certificate]
Citizen --> ProfileView : [View Profile]
Citizen --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state DocumentUpload
DocumentUpload : entry / Upload Documents
DocumentUpload : do / Validate the Details
DocumentUpload : exit / Continue or End

DocumentUpload --> DocumentUpload : [Continue]
DocumentUpload --> SessionEnd : [End]

state CertificateApplication
CertificateApplication : entry / Apply for a Certificate
CertificateApplication : do / Validate the Details
CertificateApplication : exit / Request Sent

CertificateApplication --> MultipleCertificates : [Multiple Certificates]
CertificateApplication --> IssueCert : [Issue Certificate]
CertificateApplication --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state MultipleCertificates
MultipleCertificates : entry / Apply for Multiple Certificates
MultipleCertificates : do / Validate the Details
MultipleCertificates : exit / Request Sent

MultipleCertificates --> IssueCert : [Issue Certificate]
MultipleCertificates --> RegistrarRequest : [Registrar Request]
MultipleCertificates --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state Registrar
Registrar : entry / Logged In
Registrar : do / Display Options
Registrar : exit / End Session

Registrar --> CertificateRequest : [Request for Certificates]
Registrar --> MultipleCertificateRequest : [Multiple Requests]
Registrar --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state CertificateRequest
CertificateRequest : entry / Request for Certificates
CertificateRequest : do / Validate the Details
CertificateRequest : exit / Request Sent

CertificateRequest --> IssueCert : [Issue Certificate]
CertificateRequest --> RegistrarMultipleRequests : [More Requests]
CertificateRequest --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state MultipleCertificateRequest
MultipleCertificateRequest : entry / More Requests
MultipleCertificateRequest : do / Validate the Details
MultipleCertificateRequest : exit / Request Sent

MultipleCertificateRequest --> IssueCert : [Issue Certificate]
MultipleCertificateRequest --> RegistrarMultipleRequests : [More Requests]
MultipleCertificateRequest --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state ProfileView
ProfileView : entry / View Profile
ProfileView : do / Display the Profile
ProfileView : exit / Exit from Profile Viewing

ProfileView --> EndSession : [End]

state IssueCert
IssueCert : entry / Validate Details
IssueCert : do / Issue Certificate
IssueCert : exit / Update Database

IssueCert --> MultipleCertificates : [Multiple Certificates]
IssueCert --> SessionEnd : [Logout]

state SessionEnd
SessionEnd : entry / To End Session
SessionEnd : do / End the Session
SessionEnd : exit / End

@enduml
